baci-property.description: Get the flow reading for the thermal interlock airflow sensor. This currently implemented as a flow sitch rather tan a sensor so the returned value will be toggle between OK (5V) and ERROR (0V). The return value is left as a float to allow the future implementation of an actual sensor.

baci-property.description: Return an indication that one of the interlocks sensors (temeprature or flow) has failed. 0 (OK), 1 (Error).

baci-property.description: Get the load percentage of the interlock glitch integrator. Once the integrator reaches a predefined threshold the status of the glitch counter is changed to triggered.

baci-property.description: Return the indication that the final shutdown counter has been triggered. The power supply will cut power within 32 s after this counter has been triggered. This shutdown CANNOT be cancelled. 0 (OK), 1 (Triggered).
